U.S. Agriculture SecretaryRichard Lyng will ask the Japanese Government to remove allbeef import restrictions when he visits there next month.    Lyng's remarks came in a speech at Oklahoma StateUniversity today.    "We think Japanese consumers should have the same freedomof choice as our consumers. Look at all the Japanese camerasand tape recorders in this room. We know they'd buy more beefif they had the opportunity," Lyng said. Reuter&#3;